               <head>Afghan genealogy, 2 untitled works</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85053742 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85001521">
                  <summary>Collection of prose works on Afghan genealogy written before the 19th cent.; transcribed in good scribal nastaʿlīq possibly by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7771" role="scr">Khvush Qalam</persName>
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3775-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="40v">ff. 1r-40v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on Afghan genealogy, described within the work as <q>īn risālah dar bayān-i kayfiyat-i ḥasab va nasab-i Afghān maʿlūm kardan ast</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Note at beginning, probably by William Anderson, states, <q>Genealogical history of the Afghans - copied at Kundahar, WA</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Transcription incorrect and full of omissions </p>
                        <p>IOL stamp absent </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3775-item2">
                     <locus from="41r" to="60v">ff. 41r-60v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on Afghan genealogy, described within the work as <q>īn risālah dar z̲ikr-i aḥvāl-i ansāb-i Afghānān mushtamil bar chahār bāb ast</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 60v): Nasab'nāmah-'i Afghānān completed in Muḥarram 1256/March 1840</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
